      "title": "Creating a File ✍️",
      "content": "To create an empty file, use the `touch` command:",
      "codeSnippet": "touch hello.txt",
      "codeLanguage": "bash",
      "canRunCode": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s_l3_2",
      "type": "code",
      "title": "Making a Folder 📂",
      "content": "To create a new directory (folder), use `mkdir`:",
      "codeSnippet": "mkdir secrets",
      "codeLanguage": "bash",
      "canRunCode": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s_l3_3",
      "type": "code",
      "title": "Reading a File 👀",
      "content": "To see the contents of a file without opening an editor, use `cat` (Concatenate):",
      "codeSnippet": "cat hello.txt",
      "codeLanguage": "bash",
      "canRunCode": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s_l3_4",
      "type": "code",
      "title": "Deleting Files 🗑️",
      "content": "To delete a file, use `rm` (Remove):\n\n**Warning**: There is no 'Trash Can' in the terminal. Once deleted, it's gone!",
      "codeSnippet": "rm hello.txt",
      "codeLanguage": "bash",
      "canRunCode": true
    },
